legacy.full_text: Yesterday I met with Acting Foreign Minister of Afghanistan Amir Khan Muttaqi and exchanged views on the bilateral relations. https://t.co/D12duz0Uis
Yesterday I met with Acting Minister of Refugees and Repatriations of Afghanistan Khalil Haqqani and exchanged views on humanitarian aid cooperation. https://t.co/rYwV92ABiw

On October 23rd, I met with Acting Deputy Foreign Minister of Afghanistan Mohammad Abbas Stanekzai and, on behalf of the Chinese Embassy in Afghanistan, handed over humanitarian cash assistance of US$50,000 to support Afghanistan in earthquake relief work.
Today I met with Leonard Zulu, UNHCR Representative to Afghanistan, and exchanged views on the current situation in Afghanistan and strengthening cooperation between both sides.

The Chinese government pledged a total of 30 million yuan(approximately US$4.1 million) in emergency humanitarian assistance. Plus US$ 200,000 cash assistance and 500,000 yuan of material supplies from the Red Cross society of China. https://t.co/JPWE6gm4V8

legacy.full_text: The first batch of China's earthquake relief supplies has arrived in Herat this morning. https://t.co/Mt7FSGJXz9
Today I attended the handover ceremony of China's aid to Afghanistan earthquake relief supplies and expressed China's solidarity with people of Afghanistan. https://t.co/ICPM7Scy9D

Today, I met with Mohammad Abbas Stanekzai, Acting Deputy Foreign Minister of Afghanistan, and handed over messages of condolences on the earthquake disaster in Afghanistan, from Li Qiang, Premier of the State Council of the People’s Republic of China ...
... and Foreign Minister Wang Yi, to Mohammad Hasan Akhund, Acting Prime Minister of Afghanistan, and Amir Khan Mutaqi, Acting Foreign Minister of Afghanistan.
On October 9th, the Chinese Embassy in Afghanistan handed over an emergency humanitarian cash assistance of US$200,000 provided by the Red Cross Society of China. https://t.co/Mi7Z3mAvsS
In response to the earthquake disaster in Herat Province, to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Afghanistan and the Afghan Red Crescent Society.

China International Development Cooperation Agency Spokesperson’s Remarks on the Earthquakes in Afghanistan:  We express our condolences to the serious casualties and property losses caused by the earthquake in Afghanistan,
and are willing to provide emergency humanitarian assistance according to the needs of the victims.
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesperson’s Remarks on the Earthquakes in Afghanistan:

China noted that the devastating earthquakes which hit Herat province in Afghanistan caused heavy casualties. We deeply mourn for the victims and offer our sincere sympathies to the injured and the families who have lost loved ones.

We believe that the people of Afghanistan will overcome the impact of the disaster and rebuild their homes at an early date. We will do our best to assist in Afghanistan’s disaster-relief efforts in light of its needs.
China International Development Cooperation Agency Spokesperson’s Remarks on the Earthquakes in Afghanistan:
It's very sad to hear terrible earthquake hit Herat today. We express our condolences to the families of the victims and the injured, wish the injured a speedy recovery.

Today Member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and Foreign Minister Wang Yi met with H.E. Mr. Mawlawi Amir Khan Muttaqi, Acting Foreign Minister of Afghanistan at the 3rd Trans-Himalaya Forum for International Cooperation in Nyingchi, Xizang.1/3 https://t.co/LYFDHB7Kt9
Wang Yi reiterated China’s “Three Respects” and “Three Nevers” on Afghanistan and said that China will as always support Afghanistan to build an inclusive political structure...2/3

...and is willing to continue helping Afghanistan develop relations with neighboring countries and better integrate into regional economic cooperation. Wang Yi also praised Afghan athletes for their performance at the 19th Asian Games in Hangzhou.3/3
